    <prp:code/>
    <prp:abstract>This project will be the first to fully ascertain whether the molecular cores toward the W75N region truly exhibit clear oxygen and nitrogen chemical differentiation. Previous low-resolution studies have indicated that complex chemical formation may be spatially mediated by the O/N differentiation in this region. In 4 hours of observations with ALMA, this project will be able to answer 10 years of questions on the distribution and morphology of molecular emission toward W75N including: 1) do all large O-bearing molecules map in the same region toward the same hot core sources; 2) do all the N-bearing molecules map in the same region and why are large organic N-bearing molecules that are prevalent in Orion apparently absent; and, finally 3) what species map and what does that tell us about their formation? ALMA Cycle 2 is the only telescope in the world that can provide the necessary sensitivity and resolution needed for these measurements. </prp:abstract>
